ibel- und Klassikerzitaten, Sprichwörtern, Redensarten, Fabelakteuren, Themen, Moralia und Erzähltypen erschließen diese einzigartige Fundgrube frühneuzeitlicher Erzählkunst.  aWith more than 22,000 verses, the Esopus of the former monk and protestant pastor Burkard Waldis is the most comprehensive collection of German fables of the 16th century. The first volume contains the 400 animal fables of Aesop, jokes and anecdotes edited in accordance with the first edition from 1548. The second volume provides an introduction and extensive annotations as well as the reprint of the numerous Latin versions. Extensive indices make this narrative treasury from the Reformation era accessible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFables, Greek. 4aEdition. 4aFabel / Sammlung. 4aReformationszeit. 4aWaldis, Burkhard. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aEdition.  aFable/Collection.  aReformation.  aWaldis, Burkhard.1 aLieb, Ludger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMohr, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVögel, Herfried, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311023454140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025475440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110254754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110254754/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyt